[[div style="border:solid 1px #112211; background:#EEF6EE; padding: 20px; margin-bottom: 3px;"]]

[[div_ class="fancyborder"]]

[[=image https://i.imgur.com/JUJVeOG.png class="scene-break"]]

Greetings, new Wanderer and new initiate of the Serpent's Hand.

Like all Wanderers, you were driven to the Library's halls -- rightly, to be sure -- as a refuge from the imprisonment which the Jailors impose upon the occult within the Normal World; a safe-haven for all those magical persons who would otherwise be detained and locked away or expatriated to some Nexus or other cast-out dimensional extremity. But in time, you will learn that there is a twofold meaning to the name Jailor. You will learn that not only do they imprison the occult within their new normalcy, but conceal that tiny bubble of false-sanity from the vast grandeur of the Real World and tuck it away from the Truth. Will learn that not only does the Iron Veil subjugate and choke out those traces of magic and whimsy left within the Normal World, but draw the false boundary that separates the part from the whole, and keeps so ignorant the populace in that tiny sector of the Earth where normalcy does reign that they believe their sanitized, curated habitat is Gaia's only child -- that its isolation and artificiality represent the norm rather than the exception, and nothing else of the World exists beyond them.

You shall learn that the whole of what you know to be Earth is but a sector of the World Body, excised unjustly from the rest of Terra Mater by drill and scalpel, cauterized, and deposited within the sterile, lifeless container that is the Jailor's aberrant normality. But for every such wound, the Hand will teach you that there is the path to healing. Rest assured, we will open the Ways to the thaumic world for all to see and use, until those who seek refuge and use our services to fight for their freedom become so multitudinous in rank that the Library's halls are filled to the brim with their cries; until the Jailors become unable to ignore the unsustainable costs of sustaining their subjugation and are forced to give way.

We have attached the volume below to catch you up and aid your process of reintegration with all our brothers and sisters on the other side of the Veil. You have completed the most difficult obstacle in merely declaring yourself Hand; now seek out the Library and the Ways will open to your needs. Walk with caution and prudence the tightrope between realms of fire and ice, [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/incident-report-x23 be not seduced by the dark nor blinded by the light] -- concern yourself only with keeping this temperance, and be assured the Library will find you.

- [[size 140%]]**L.S.**[[/size]]
[[/div]]

[[/div]]


@@ @@


[[div_ class="fancyhr"]]
